@startuml auction-state
title Auction State Diagram

[*] --> DRAFT : Seller begins\ncreating auction

DRAFT --> SCHEDULED : Seller submits\nvalid auction form

DRAFT --> [*] : Seller discards draft

SCHEDULED --> ACTIVE : Scheduled start\ntime arrives\n(Quartz job fires)

SCHEDULED --> CANCELLED : Seller cancels\nbefore start\n[no bids exist]

ACTIVE --> ACTIVE : Bid placed in\nlast 30 seconds\n/ extend by 2 min\n(anti-snipe)

ACTIVE --> ENDED : Scheduled end\ntime arrives

ACTIVE --> CANCELLED : Admin intervention\n(policy violation)

ENDED --> SOLD : Highest bid\n>= reserve price\n/ select winner,\ntrigger payment

ENDED --> CLOSED_NO_SALE : No bids OR\nhighest bid\n< reserve price\n/ notify seller

SOLD --> [*] : Transaction\ncompleted

CLOSED_NO_SALE --> RELISTED : Seller chooses\nto relist item

RELISTED --> SCHEDULED : New auction\ncreated for same item

CANCELLED --> [*] : Auction archived

note right of ACTIVE
  Anti-snipe rule:
  any bid in last 30s
  extends end time by 2 min.
  Extensions are unlimited.
end note

note right of SOLD
  Payment Service takes over.
  Auction record is archived
  after transaction closes.
end note

@enduml
